]]\nFile:Wyoming poster.jpg|''[[Wyoming]]'' (1940) with [[Marjorie Main]]\nFile:Hollywood steps out (28).png|''[[Hollywood Steps Out]]'' (1941), left to right: [[William Powell]], [[Spencer Tracy]], [[Ronald Colman]] and [[Errol Flynn]]. Seated: Wallace Beery and [[C. Aubrey Smith]]\nFile:Wallace Beery in Barnacle Bill (1941).png|''[[Barnacle Bill (1941 film)|Barnacle Bill]]'' (1941)\n</gallery>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n[[Academy Awards]] \n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\"\n|-style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\"\n! Year\n! Award\n! Film\n! Result\n|-\n||[[3rd Academy Awards|1929-1930]] \n| [[Academy Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]]\n| ''[[The Big House (1930 film)|The Big House]]''\n| {{nominated}} \n|-\n||[[57th Academy Awards|1931-1932]] \n| [[Academy Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]]\n| ''[[The Champ (1931 film)|The Champ]]''\n| {{Won}} (\"Tied\" with [[Fredric March]] for ''[[Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde (1931 film)|Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde]]'' <small>\n|-\n|} \n\n[[Venice Film Festival]] \n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\"\n|-style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\"\n! Year\n! Award\n! Film\n! Result\n|-\n|1934\n| [[Venice Film Festival Award for Best Actor|Volpi Cup for Best Actor]]\n| ''[[Viva Villa!]]''\n| {{Won}} \n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of actors with Academy Award nominations]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em|refs=\n\n<ref name=\"Sonneborn 2002\">{{Cite book|title= A to Z of American Women in the Performing Arts |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Yf2741A_BkYC&pg=PA205&lpg=PA205&dq=%22beery |last=Sonneborn |first=Liz |date=2014-05-14 |publisher=[[Infobase Publishing]] |publication-date=2002 |isbn=9781438107905 |oclc=297504194 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Long-Beach-Independent 1948 Apr 29\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/47736809/links-beery-to-physician/ |title=Links Beery to Physician |newspaper=[[Long Beach Independent]] |location=Los Angeles |date=April 29, 1948 |page=12 |access-date=2020-03-31 |via=Newspapers.com}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"LATimes 1949 Nov 18\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/47736926/court-rejects-claim-against-beery/ |title=Court Rejects Claim Beery Millions |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=November 18, 1949 |page=I17 |access-date=2020-03-31 |via=Newspapers.com}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Schumm-v-Berg\">[https://scocal.stanford.edu/opinion/schumm-v-berg-26378 \"Johan Richard Wallace Schumm, a Minor, etc., Appellant, ''v'' Phil Berg, Beery's agent) and Noah Beery, Jr. (Beery's nephew), as Executors of the Estate of Wallace Beery, Jr.\"] (opinion of Justice [[Jesse W. Carter]]), citation: 37 Cal.2d 174 (1951), Supreme Court California Resources, [[Stanford Law School]], Robert Crown Law Library<div style=\"margin-left:2em\">(Philip Jay Berg, 1902\u20131983, was married to actress [[Leila Hyams]])</div></ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Johann-Schumm-photos 1952\">2 Photographs of Mrs. Gloria Schumm and son, Johann Schumm (age 4), April 17, 1952; {{OCLC|822257200|857831052|663235176}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Miller 2002\">''[https://books.google.com/books?id=rmvzyPI4h00C&pg=PA20&lpg=PA20&dq=%22schumm Ardor in the Court!: Sex and the Law,]'' by Jeffrey Miller (born 1950), [[ECW Press]] (2002); {{OCLC|972272320}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"ChicagoTribune 2002 Apr 4\">[http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2002-04-04/features/0204040003_1_three-stooges-moe-howard-shemp-howard \"A nyuk on the wild side: Did the Three Stooges Cover Up the Murder of Their Founder?,\"] by Jim Mueller, ''[[Chicago Tribune]]'', April 4, 2002 (retrieved September 3, 2017)</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Fleming 2005\">''[https://books.google.com/books?id=f0usSUISUUMC&pg=PA176&lpg=PA176&dq=%22beery The Fixers: Eddie Mannix, Howard Strickling, and the 